      "Based on the search results, here's what I found about the Claude Code 2.1.0, 2.1.1, and 2.1.2 releases in January 2026:\n\n## Release Timeline\n\n**Claude Code 2.1 series was released in early January 2026**, with rapid successive updates:\n- **2.1.0**: Major update from 2.0.76\n- **2.1.1**: Quick hotfix (released shortly after 2.1.0)\n- **2.1.2**: Additional security fixes and improvements\n\n## Key Highlights\n\n### Massive Update Scale\nThe 2.1.0 release included **1,096 commits** - an exceptionally large update that caught the attention of the developer community. The changelog was so long it \"scrolls for several screens,\" prompting jokes about whether Anthropic was using AI tools to write their code.\n\n### Major Features in 2.1.0\n\n1. **Skills Hot Reload** - Previously, modifying custom skill files required restarting the entire session. Now changes take effect immediately when you save files in `~/.claude/skills` or `.claude/skills` directories. This was described as \"the most praised feature by international users.\"\n\n2. **Three-level Hooks Nesting** - Enhanced lifecycle hooks that can automatically trigger actions before/after tool executions, with more granular control than before.\n\n3. **Overall Improvements**:\n   - 30+ new features\n   - 40+ bug fixes\n   - 10+ performance optimizations\n\n### Security Fixes (2.1.1 & 2.1.2)\n\nThe rapid follow-up releases addressed a **critical security vulnerability** in 2.1.0:\n- Sensitive data (OAuth tokens, API keys, passwords) could leak into debug logs\n- Fixed OAuth token refresh timing issues\n- Resolved concurrent token refresh bugs\n\n### Additional Features\n- **Multi-language support**: Users can configure their preferred language (Chinese, Japanese, Spanish, French, etc.) in `settings.json`\n- **Improved Agent resilience**: Agents now adapt when tool calls are rejected rather than stopping completely\n\n### Installation\nUsers can upgrade via:\n```bash\nnpm update -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\n```\n\nThe release was significant enough that one article described it as \"2.1 and pre-2.1 versions are completely different species,\" emphasizing the substantial improvements in this January 2026 release wave."
