            "title": "Claude Code 2.1.2超详细更新说明，小白也能10分钟上手",
            "url": "https://juejin.cn/post/7592892218669187106"
          },
          {
            "title": "Claude Code 2.1.1 震撼发布：1096个提交，重新定义AI编程助手的生产力",
            "url": "https://baijiahao.baidu.com/s?id=1853815198640811192"
          }
        ]
      },
      "Based on my web search, I found comprehensive information about the **Claude Code 2.1** release. Here's a summary of the key details:\n\n## Claude Code 2.1 Release Overview\n\n**Release Date:** January 2026 (2.1.0 released around January 7-12, with rapid follow-up versions 2.1.1 and 2.1.2)\n\n**Scale:** Major update with **1,096 code commits**\n\n## Major Features & Improvements\n\n### 1. **Skills Hot Reload** ⭐ (Most Popular Feature)\n- Previously required session restart to modify skills\n- Now changes to skills in `~/.claude/skills` or `.claude/skills` take effect immediately\n- File system monitoring + hot loading significantly improves development efficiency\n\n### 2. **Enhanced Hooks System**\n- **PreToolUse/PostToolUse hooks** - Automatically trigger actions before/after tool execution\n- Support for three-level nested hooks\n- Can now be configured at Agent and Skill frontmatter level, not just globally\n- Enables automated workflows like logging, SAST scanning, result validation\n\n### 3. **Agent Capabilities**\n- **Isolated sub-agent contexts** - Prevents sub-agent operations from interfering with main agent state\n- **Intelligent error recovery** - When tool calls are rejected, agents now propose alternative solutions instead of failing\n- **/plan mode** - Direct shortcut to planning mode\n- **Wildcard tool permissions** - Simplified permission configuration (e.g., grant access to entire config directories)\n\n### 4. **Multi-language Support**\n- Native language configuration via `settings.json`:\n  ```json\n  {\n    \"language\": \"chinese\"\n  }\n  ```\n- Supports Chinese, Japanese, Spanish, French, etc.\n- Eliminates need to repeatedly specify language in prompts\n\n### 5. **Terminal & UX Improvements**\n- **Shift+Enter** for multi-line input now works out-of-the-box across major terminals (iTerm2, WezTerm, Ghostty, Kitty, etc.)\n- Enhanced Vim mode with new text objects and shortcuts\n- Real-time reasoning visualization\n- Improved slash command completion (triggers from any position)\n\n### 6. **Performance & Security**\n- **3x reduction** in memory usage for large conversations\n- Security fix for sensitive information leakage in debug logs (OAuth tokens, API keys, passwords)\n- OAuth-related bug fixes (token refresh timing, concurrent refresh issues)\n\n### 7. **MCP (Model Context Protocol) Integration**\n- Native support for MCP protocol\n- Direct connection to enterprise data sources without API wrappers\n- Example: `@k8s-cluster` for real-time Pod status, Event logs, and Metrics\n\n### 8. **Additional Features**\n- `/teleport` for remote session synchronization\n- `respectGitignore` for project-controlled @-mention file selection\n- `IS_DEMO` mode to hide sensitive info during live recordings\n- `Ctrl+B` for running bash+agent tasks in background\n- Long text auto-continuation when hitting token limits\n\n## Version History\n- **2.1.0** - Major feature release (1000+ commits)\n- **2.1.1** - Hotfix for security vulnerability (109 CLI issues fixed)\n- **2.1.2** - Additional stability fixes\n\n## How to Upgrade\n```bash\nnpm update -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\nclaude --version  # Verify version shows 2.1.x\n```\n\n## Availability\nAvailable to Claude Pro, Max, and Enterprise users\n\nThis release marks Claude Code's evolution from an \"AI programming assistant\" to a **\"programmable agent infrastructure\"** platform, enabling developers to build persistent, modular AI workflows with significantly improved capabilities."
