bility & Requirements\n- **Available to**: Copilot Pro, Pro+, Business, and Enterprise paid subscribers\n- **Supported Platforms**: \n  - VS Code (chat, editing, and intelligent agents)\n  - GitHub.com (web interface)\n  - Mobile apps\n  - CLI (Command Line Interface)\n  - Coding Agent environments\n- **Enterprise Setup**: Business administrators must manually enable the feature in their settings/policies for team access\n\n### 🎯 Strategic Context\n- This update came shortly after Anthropic's release of Claude Opus 4.6\n- The release emphasizes GitHub's multi-model strategy to maintain competitiveness in the AI coding assistant market\n- Focus on speed improvements addresses previous user pain points about slow AI code generation\n\n### 📅 Related Timeline\n- **February 8, 2025**: GitHub announced a series of major Copilot updates and showcased Copilot's future vision for greater autonomy\n- The GPT-5.3-Codex rollout represents part of GitHub's broader strategy to enhance Copilot's autonomous capabilities\n\nThis February 2025 update marks a significant performance leap for GitHub Copilot, particularly benefiting developers working on complex, large-scale projects where speed and workflow efficiency are critical.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
