g Anthropic's **Claude 3.5 Sonnet** and Google's **Gemini 1.5 Pro**.\n\n### 3. **Major Feature Update Announcement** (February 8, 2025)\nGitHub announced **\"a series of major updates\"** to its AI programming assistant Copilot and showcased Copilot's vision for greater autonomy in the future.\n\n## Related 2025 Context\n\nWhile not specifically February, additional significant 2025 developments include:\n\n- **GPT-5 Integration** (August 2025): Full integration of OpenAI's GPT-5 series models\n- **Open Source Copilot Chat** (May 2025): Microsoft open-sourced the Copilot Chat extension code under MIT license and integrated it into Visual Studio Code\n- **Free Version Launch**: GitHub Copilot introduced a free tier with 2,000 code completions and 50 chat requests per month\n- **AI Agent Launch** (May 2025): GitHub released a Copilot AI agent that can handle specific programming tasks, including checking and modifying code in repositories\n\nThe February 2025 announcements particularly emphasized **visual capabilities** and **multi-model support**, marking GitHub's strategy to expand Copilot's capabilities beyond traditional code completion to more comprehensive AI-assisted development workflows.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
