 for real-time code quality checking\n- Support for \"click-to-edit\" functionality\n\n### Other Recent Updates (2025):\n\n**Wave 13 (Announced Late 2025)**\n- Significant upgrade to multi-agent workflows\n- Performance and accessibility improvements\n- Enhanced terminal reliability\n\n**March 29, 2025 Update**\n- Official update with improvements to real-time collaboration features\n- Multi-system support enhancements\n\n**April 2025 Updates:**\n- **New Brand Identity**: Launched a completely new visual identity and logo on April 28, 2025\n- Free tier feature upgrades\n- Browser preview functionality enabling DOM element and browser console access\n- Web research capabilities for finding documentation and solutions\n\n### Key Features Highlighted:\n- Multi-model support (GPT-4.1, Gemini 2.5, Claude Sonnet 3.7/4)\n- Multi-modal (image) input support\n- Custom workflows and team sharing\n- Netlify auto-deployment capabilities\n- VS Code and JetBrains plugin integration\n- Development container support (August 2025)\n\n**Note**: The search results don't show specific releases dated exactly in February 2025, but the Wave 4 release in early March 2025 appears to be the closest major update to your timeframe. The most active development period appears to be March-April 2025.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
