      "Based on my search results, here's what I found about Devin AI news and updates:\n\n## Key Finding: No February 2025 Updates Found\n\nThe search did not return any specific news, updates, or releases for **Devin AI in February 2025**. However, I did find important information about Devin AI's timeline:\n\n## Devin AI Timeline\n\n**December 2024**\n- Devin officially launched for teams at **$500/month** starting price\n\n**January 2025**\n- Devin 1.2 version released\n- Enhanced reasoning and command integration capabilities\n\n**April 3, 2025** (Major Release)\n- **Devin 2.0** was officially released\n- Dramatic price reduction from **$500/month to $20/month** (96% decrease)\n- New features include:\n  - Native agent-based IDE platform\n  - Multi-instance cloud IDE integration\n  - Autonomous code correction capabilities\n  - Dynamic documentation management\n  - Devin Search and Devin Wiki features\n  - Support for parallel development and intelligent planning\n\n## Key Insights\n\nThe search results indicate that **February 2025 was a quiet month for Devin AI** with no major announcements or releases. The significant activity occurred in January (version 1.2) and then in April 2025 with the major 2.0 launch.\n\n## Related Industry News (February 2025 Context)\n\nWhile not specific to Devin AI, the broader AI development tools space saw activity around this time, including:\n- Replit AI Agent 2.0 early access launch (February 25, 2025)\n- Various AI model updates from competitors like OpenAI, Anthropic, and others\n\nIf you're looking for very specific information that might not have been captured in this search, you may want to check Cognition AI's official channels, blog, or developer documentation directly."
