s, Continue.dev is described as:\n- An open-source AI code assistant (27,141+ GitHub stars as of June 2025)\n- Available for VS Code and JetBrains IDEs\n- Supports connecting any models and any context\n- Provides autocomplete and chat experiences\n- Features include:\n  - **Chat** - sidebar chat for understanding and iterating on code\n  - **Autocomplete** - inline code suggestions as you type\n  - **Edit** - modify code without leaving your current file\n  - **Agent** - make substantial changes to your codebase\n\n### Recent Support Additions\nThe search results mention support for various AI models including DeepSeek-R1, Qwen2.5-7B, and improved retrieval models with Voyage embeddings/reranking capabilities.\n\n**Note**: While the search didn't return a detailed changelog specifically for February 2025 releases, the most concrete February 2025 reference is the IDEA plugin version 0.0.88 released on February 24, 2025. For the most up-to-date and detailed release information, I'd recommend checking the official [Continue.dev GitHub repository](https://github.com/continuedev/continue) or [docs.continue.dev](https://docs.continue.dev).\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
