ikely explains why no February 2025 changelog exists.\n\n## Key Updates Around That Period\n\nHere are the notable Codex CLI updates I found from 2025:\n\n### **August 2025 Updates** (Closest documented releases)\n\n1. **v0.23.0 (August 21, 2025)**\n   - Added dynamic model switching functionality\n   - `/model` command to list and select available models\n   - Support for gpt-5-high model option\n\n2. **Major Update (August 8, 2025)**\n   - **GPT-5 became the default model** for Codex CLI\n   - Integration with ChatGPT subscription (Plus, Pro, Team plans)\n   - No separate API key required\n   - Enhanced prompts and execution framework\n   - Improved approval workflows and sandbox logic\n   - Updated terminal user interface\n\n3. **v0.36.0 (September 16, 2025)**\n   - Integrated **GPT-5-Codex model**\n   - Improved code generation speed and reasoning quality\n   - AGENTS.md file support for behavior control\n   - Session recovery capabilities\n   - JSON-RPC and MCP interface extensions\n\n## Recommendation\n\nIf you're looking for the most recent changelog information, I suggest checking the official sources directly:\n\n- **GitHub Repository**: https://github.com/openai/codex/releases\n- **Official Documentation**: https://openai.com/index/introducing-upgrades-to-codex/\n\nWould you like me to search for more recent updates or specific features of Codex CLI?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
