n- **Stable releases**: Every Tuesday at UTC 2000 (promotion of previous week's preview + bug fixes)\n- **Nightly releases**: Daily at UTC 0000\n\n## Timeline Context\n\nBased on the available information:\n\n1. **June 2025** - Initial public launch of Gemini CLI as a free, open-source AI coding tool\n2. **July 2025** - Early updates including audio/video support and Markdown enhancements\n3. **August 2025** - Major updates like VSCode integration and MCP protocol enhancements (v0.1.20)\n\n**Note on February 2025:** The search results indicate that **Gemini CLI was not publicly released until June 2025**. The project was announced by Google in June 2025, which means there would be no official changelog for February 2025 as the tool did not exist publicly at that time.\n\n## For Most Recent Information\n\nTo get the latest changelog and updates, I recommend:\n1. Visiting the official GitHub repository: `https://github.com/google-gemini/gemini-cli/releases`\n2. Checking the [Releases documentation](https://github.com/google-gemini/gemini-cli/blob/main/docs/releases.md) for detailed release notes\n\nWould you like me to search for more specific information about a particular time period or feature of Gemini CLI?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
